  <p><span class="nnv">
    <!--Drip Content--> <a href="/cs/schizophrenia/"><strong>Schizophrenia Resources</strong></a><br> Resources concerning schizophrenia and similar severe brain disorders. </span></p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/weblogsblogs/index.htm"><strong>Mental Health WebLogs</strong></a><br> Weblogs (or blogs, or simply Journals) from all over that relate to mental health issues. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/eat/"><strong>Eating Disorders</strong></a><br> Eating disorders such as anorexia nervosa and bulimia are more common in women, but men sometimes develop these disorders too. There are Online resources that can help, but face-to-face help is usually needed. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/personaltydisordrs/"><strong>Personality Disorder Resources</strong></a><br> Heavily weighted toward Borderline Personality Disorder, possibly because of the popularity of this diagnosis and the controversy surrounding its use. These disorders include Borderline, Antisocial, Schizoid, Schizotypal, Avoidant, Histrionic, Narcissistic, Obsessive-Compulsive, Paranoid Personality Disorders. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/aging/"><strong>Seniors &amp; Aging</strong></a><br> As we get older life seems to get better. There are also unique issues that arise in our senior years. Here are resources that will help you stay mentally healthy as you age. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/psychopharmacology/"><strong>Psychiatric Medications</strong></a><br> Sites with information on medications used in mental health treatment: antidepressants, antianxiety medications, antipsychotic medications, and others. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/sexaddict/index.htm"><strong>Cyber Addictions</strong></a><br> Some people seem to have a problem with Internet sexual activity and even with compulsive Internet use. Are these true addictions? This remains a controversial area. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/selfhelp/"><strong>Self-Help Resources</strong></a><br> Informational sites to help you understand mental health issues. Learn about a friend's diagnosis or help yourself solve problems in your life. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/ocd/"><strong>Obsessive-Compulsive Disorder</strong></a><br> Sites concerning OCD and treatments which are effective. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/psychotherapy/"><strong>Psychotherapy</strong></a><br> Sites with a focus on counseling and psychotherapy. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/depression/"><strong>Depression Resources</strong></a><br> Material that focuses on depression and bipolar disorder (manic-depression). Some of the best material at About.com and elsewhere on the Internet. Treatment can include antidepressant medications such as Prozac, Zoloft, Paxil, Celexa, Welbutrin and St. John's Wort - and it can also include psychotherapy. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/specialtechniques/"><strong>Special Techniques</strong></a><br> Sites which focus on specialized techniques such as hypnosis, EMDR, and NLP. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/stressmanagement/"><strong>Stress Management Resources</strong></a><br> Learn how to manage the stress in your life.&nbsp; Here are resources to help you relax and learn not to worry. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/anxietypanic/"><strong>Anxiety &amp; Panic Resources</strong></a><br> Information to help you learn about and cope with anxiety, panic disorder, PTSD, phobias, and related problems. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/academicpsychology/"><strong>Academic Psychology Resources</strong></a><br> These are sites of interest to students and professors in Psychology programs. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/budgetmentalhealth/"><strong>Budget Mental Health</strong></a><br> Free medications, other assistance for mental health treatment. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/chemicaldependency/"><strong>Chemical Dependency Resources</strong></a><br> Sites which focus on information about and recovery from drug and alcohol problems. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/collegeuniversity/"><strong>College and University Resources</strong></a><br> Psychology Departments and related programs. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/computerstuff/"><strong>Computers and Mental Health</strong></a><br> Sites focusing on using computers in mental health, and mental health aspects of computer use. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/traumaptsd/"><strong>Trauma &amp; PTSD Resources</strong></a><br> These sites include information on surviving different types of trauma including combat, child abuse, and disasters. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/mensmentalhealth/"><strong>Men's Mental Health Resources</strong></a><br> Sites which focus on men's issues and fatherhood. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/continuinged/"><strong>Continuing Education Resources</strong></a><br> Mental Health continuing education is becoming available Online. Here is a growing list of places where mental health professionals can keep up to date on the latest research and practice. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/crisis/"><strong>Crisis Intervention</strong></a><br> Organizations and resources for those intervening in cases of trauma or disaster. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/griefandmourning/"><strong>Death, Grief and Mourning Resources</strong></a><br> Resources for the dying and those surviving a loss and for professionals who work with these people. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/culturalissue1/"><strong>Cultural Issues</strong></a><br> Mental health professionals often need to understanding cultural aspects of issues. These links will provide you with insights into a multitude of cultures and thought-provoking diversity issues. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/familyresources/"><strong>Family Resources</strong></a><br> Sites about children and family issues. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/dissociative/"><strong>Dissociative Disorders</strong></a><br> Dissociative disorders such as Dissociative Identity Disorder (multiple personality disorder) usually result from trauma or abuse in early childhood. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/gaylesbian/"><strong>Gay, Lesbian &amp; Bisexual Sites</strong></a><br> Sites which focus on issues and support for gay, lesbian, bisexual, and transgender persons. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/associations/"><strong>Associations and Institutions</strong></a><br> Mental health agencies and institutions of interest to professionals, consumers, and families. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/localandregional/"><strong>Local and Regional Resources</strong></a><br> Mental Health Resources in your state, town or region </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/managedcare/"><strong>Managed Care Issues</strong></a><br> Mental Health has been especially impacted by managed care.&nbsp; Here are some resources in this field. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/siteswservices1/"><strong>E-Therapy, and Sites Offering Services</strong></a><br> On these pages are sites that actually deliver services over the Internet.&nbsp; Be careful. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/onlinejournals/"><strong>Journals and Publications</strong></a><br> These publications either have a table of contents online, some content online, or an ability to browse abstracts.&nbsp; </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/mft/index.htm"><strong>Counseling, Marriage &amp; Family Therapy</strong></a><br> Resources about counseling and marriage &amp; family therapy. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/legalissuessw/"><strong>Legal Issues in Mental Health</strong></a><br> The law and mental health interact in complex ways. Some laws require confidentiality while others require information to be revealed. Here are some resources that help sort out these issues. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/health/index.htm"><strong>Health and Rehab Psychology</strong></a><br> Mental health professionals are often employed in health care and rehabilitation settings. Here are resources related to mental health and physical illness and disability. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/software/"><strong>Mental Health Software</strong></a><br> Software for clinicians, students, researchers, and consumers. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/mindandbody/"><strong>Mind and Body</strong></a><br> These sites all focus on the relationship between mind and body. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/psychiatryresourc/"><strong>Psychiatry Resources</strong></a><br> Sites of interest to psychiatrists and others interested in psychiatry. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/sexuality/"><strong>Sexuality Resources</strong></a><br> Online resources that focus on some aspect of human sexuality, but no erotica or porn. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/spirituality1/"><strong>Spiritual Resources</strong></a><br> Nurture your spirit with these resources. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/biofeedback/"><strong>Biofeedback Resources</strong></a><br> Resources with information about biofeedback and self-regulation. This technique can be used for headaches, chronic pain, anxiety and ADD. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/suicideresources/"><strong>Suicide Resources</strong></a><br> Covering all aspects of suicide and suicide prevention. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/theororientations/"><strong>Theoretical Orientations</strong></a><br> Information about different schools of psychology: theoretical orientations from behaviorism to Freudian. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/privatepractice/"><strong>Private Practice Resources</strong></a><br> Issues and resources specific to the mental health professional in private practice. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/lcswcounselingmft/"><strong>Social Work Resources</strong></a><br> Resources about Social Work and Social Workers. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/womensmentalhealth/"><strong>Women's Mental Health Resources</strong></a><br> Women have unique mental health needs and problems. Here are health and mental health resources that focus on women. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/abuse/index.htm"><strong>Abuse - Child, Elder &amp; Domestic</strong></a><br> Resources concerning child abuse, elder abuse, and domestic violence. These problems are now less hidden than in the past, but the effects are still horrendous. All abuse is preventable. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/productreviews/index.htm"><strong>Reviews of Mental Health Books/Tapes</strong></a><br> Here are my opinions about mental health books and other products related to mental health. You may not always agree, but you can be assured that I will write an honest review. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/corporatemntlhlth/"><strong>Corporate Mental Health</strong></a><br> Sites for making corporate environments more healthy. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/consumersites/"><strong>Consumer Sites</strong></a><br> These original features explore sites created by persons struggling with mental disorders or other problems. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/toppicks/index.htm"><strong>Top Picks in Mental Health Products</strong></a><br> Here are some of my recommendations for mental health books and related products. There are lots of them out there. Here are some of the best. </p>
  <p> <a href="/cs/comprehensivesites/"><strong>Comprehensive Mental Health Resources</strong></a><br> Here are some resources which cover the broad areas of mental health. </p>
